metadata.name: Pearl Jam | Moore Theatre Marquee | January 17, 1992
metadata.description:
The Pearl Jam concert that took place on January 17, 1992, at The Moore Theatre in Seattle, Washington, is considered an iconic and significant performance in the band's early career. At that time, Pearl Jam was just beginning to gain widespread recognition following the release of their debut album, "Ten."

I never got to see a shows there.  Did not make it to this Pearl Jam show.  Drove by it many times.  Shot this photo and was bummed that I could not make it to the show for what ever stupid reason.  Miss those days!

The Moore Theatre is a historic venue in Seattle known for its intimate setting, which was well-suited for the band's energetic and raw performance style. This particular show holds a special place in Pearl Jam's history because it was filmed for their music video "Jeremy," which later became one of their most well-known songs.

It was a pivotal moment in the band's career. It captured their raw energy, showcased their talent, and helped propel them to greater success in the years to come.
